        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-04-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="167" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d167">
                <head>No. 42.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Earl <persName type="from">Granville</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Lowell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign
                                    Office</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-04-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 5,
                            1882</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                        your letter of the 3d instant, requesting that Mr. Patrick Slattery, a
                        naturalized citizen of the United States, who is detained in Limerick County
                        jail, under the; protection of person and property (Ireland) act, 1881, may
                        be brought to trial at an early date.</p>
                <p>In reply, I have the honor to state to you that I have referred this matter
                        to the proper department of Her Majesty’s Government.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GRANVILLE</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
